description: Associates a package with an Amazon ES domain.

parameters.name: PackageID
parameters.description: Internal ID of the package that you want to associate with a domain. Use DescribePackages to find this value.

parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description: Name of the domain that you want to associate the package with.

nested_items.name: PackageName
nested_items.description: User specified name of the package.

nested_items.name: LastUpdated
nested_items.description: Timestamp of the most-recent update to the association status.

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: Name of the domain you've associated a package with.

nested_items.name: DomainPackageStatus
nested_items.description: State of the association. Values are ASSOCIATING/ASSOCIATION_FAILED/ACTIVE/DISSOCIATING/DISSOCIATION_FAILED.

nested_items.name: ReferencePath
nested_items.description: The relative path on Amazon ES nodes, which can be used as synonym_path when the package is synonym file.

nested_items.name: ErrorDetails
nested_items.description: Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null otherwise.
